The Mona Lisa, painted by Leonardo da Vinci between 1503 and 1506, is arguably the most famous and recognizable painting in the world. It is considered a masterpiece and a symbol of the High Renaissance period. The painting depicts a woman, believed to be Lisa Gherardini, sitting in a chair with a wry smile on her face. Artificial intelligence (AI) and human intelligence (HI) differ in many ways, including how they process information. AI processes information by using mathematical algorithms that allow it to recognize patterns and make predictions based on those patterns.
